ðŸš€ Creating a Password Generator Web App with React

In this project, I had the opportunity to delve into React, one of the most popular JavaScript libraries for building user interfaces. I built a simple yet powerful Password Generator Web App that demonstrates some key concepts and features of React.

Understanding React Hooks
The foundation of our project lies in React Hooks, which provide a way to use state and other React features without writing a class. We utilized several hooks such as useState, useEffect, and useRef.

useState: Used to manage state variables like the length of the password, whether to include numbers, characters, and the generated password itself.
useEffect: Employed to trigger the password generation function whenever there's a change in the inputs.
useRef: Enabled us to reference the password input field for copying the generated password to the clipboard.
Dynamic Password Generation Logic
The core functionality of our app lies in the passwordGenerator function. This function dynamically generates a random password based on the specified length and criteria (numbers, characters).

Interactive User Interface
The user interface of our app allows users to interactively customize the password generation process:

Adjust the length of the password using a range input.
Toggle inclusion of numbers and special characters using checkboxes.
View the generated password and copy it to the clipboard with a single click.
Conclusion
Building this Password Generator Web App was a fantastic learning experience in React. I gained a deeper understanding of React Hooks, state management, and building interactive user interfaces.

You can check out the full code and see the app in action on my GitHub repository:https://github.com/harshad00/Chai_With_React

